# AlphaOS — V2-FRONTIER config (rename to .env, do NOT commit)
#
# The app stores all state (sleeves, holdings, portfolio config, NAV ledger)
# in PostgreSQL (required). MinIO/S3 (below) is OPTIONAL and read-only — it is
# only used to pull daily closes for US stocks.
#
# In Kubernetes these values come from the Crunchy (CPNG) secret
# `<cluster>-pguser-<user>` — see DEPLOYMENT.md. Locally, set them here.
#
# Loader order: ALPHAOS_DATABASE_URL takes precedence over DATABASE_URL;
# if neither is set the discrete PG* parts are used.

# Either: full connection URL (a raw Crunchy `uri` works as-is; the driver
# is normalized to psycopg3 automatically).
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@your-postgres-host:5432/alphaos

# Or: the discrete parts (used when DATABASE_URL is unset).
# PGHOST=your-postgres-host
# PGPORT=5432
# PGUSER=alphaos
# PGPASSWORD=your-password
# PGDATABASE=alphaos

# --- MinIO / S3 for US-stock daily closes (OPTIONAL, read-only) ---
# Only needed for `alphaos prices refresh` / POST /api/prices/refresh, which
# marks US stocks to their latest daily close from the `stocks-us` bucket.
# Leave unset to run without pricing (US stocks stay at cost or a manual price).
# A read-only credential is sufficient; nothing is ever written to the bucket.
# MINIO_ENDPOINT_URL=https://minio.your-host:9000
# MINIO_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-read-only-access-key
# MINIO_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-read-only-secret-key
# MINIO_BUCKET=stocks-us
#
# FX rates (USD/EUR->SEK) are fetched over HTTPS from api.riksbank.se (ECB
# fallback) and cached in the DB — no env needed. If the host has no outbound
# internet, set the rates by hand in Settings instead.
